After a lifetime of heavy computer work, I'd resigned myself to not seeing "quite right" for either far, computer-distance, or up close; no matter what adjustments other optometrists made whenever I got new glasses, something was always off... Until last year, with Dr Pratt. As soon as I put them on, I was astonished at the clarity at any distance. I recommend him and his office any chance it comes up.  This year I have new glasses again. Something was off and I felt disheartened. Walked in asking if he could see me. He made time to reexamine, made some adjustments in how they fit, took the time to explain where and how to view, and it's made a world of difference.  The staff is friendly and knowledgeable. I've had glasses that would get out of shape and I'd periodically stop in to get them readjusted. They're always happy to help. Their concern for satisfied customers is evident.  Dr Pratt has also implemented a lot of technology which makes for a very efficient experience.

