Local* biz shout-out: Pet Club on Chandler -- I used to avoid shopping here, because I thought it was a posh, boutique-y sort of store, with high prices. Started going there at the recommendation of our doggie's rescue (AZ Happy Tails), as they regularly host --not sure if this particular store, but at the one in Chandler--adoption events for rescues and they help them out A LOT with food donations and more.  After shopping there several times, I can tell you that they are always friendly, helpful, carry healthful brands, and their prices are quite competitive. For instance, I ran in there just now to pick up some styptic powder and compared the price with Amazon. Pet Club was almost half the price for the same item.  * Since they have several stores, I wasn't sure if they qualified as "local," so I checked their website and I learned their corporate HQ is in Tempe. Kudos!!

